ed_confidence(entry, config, now=now)\n    difficulty_bonus = 1.0 - decayed\n    return base_boost * (1.0 + difficulty_bonus)\n```\n\n### Stability Growth (Jost's First Law)\n\nMemory half-life grows with reinforcement count:\n\n```python\n@staticmethod\ndef effective_half_life(base_half_life: int, reinforce_count: int) -> float:\n    \"\"\"Compute effective half-life with stability growth.\n    \n    base * (1.0 + log1p(reinforce_count) * 0.3)\n    \n    Example: A memory with reinforce_count=10 gets base × 1.72\n    \"\"\"\n    stability_growth = 1.0 + math.log1p(reinforce_count) * 0.3\n    return base_half_life * stability_growth\n```\n\n### Demotion Engine\n\n```python\ndef check_demotion(\n    self,\n    entry: MemoryEntry,\n    profile: MemoryProfile,\n    *,\n    now: datetime | None = None,\n) -> str | None:\n    \"\"\"Check if entry should be demoted to a lower tier.\n    \n    Returns the target tier name if demotion criteria are met, or None.\n    \n    Demotion criteria (ALL must be true):\n    - Layer defines demotion_to (not None)\n    - Effective confidence near the confidence floor (within 1.5x)\n    - No access within the layer's half-life period\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## PROFILE LOADING & RESOLUTION\n\n**File:** `C:/cursor/tapps-brain/src/tapps_brain/profile.py` (Lines 322-351)\n\n### Resolution Order\n\nProfiles are loaded in this priority order:\n\n1. **Project-specific** - `{project_dir}/.tapps-brain/profile.yaml`\n2. **User-global** - `~/.tapps-brain/profile.yaml`\n3. **Built-in** (default: `repo-brain`) - Bundled YAML files in `tapps_brain/profiles/`\n\n### Profile Functions\n\n```python\ndef resolve_profile(\n    project_dir: Path,\n    profile_name: str | None = None,\n) -> MemoryProfile:\n    \"\"\"Resolve the active profile using the resolution order.\"\"\"\n    # 1. Project-specific profile\n    project_profile = project_dir / \".tapps-brain\" / \"profile.yaml\"\n    if project_profile.exists():\n        profile = load_profile(project_profile)\n        return _resolve_inheritance(profile)\n    \n    # 2. User-global profile\n    user_profile = Path.home() / \".tapps-brain\" / \"profile.yaml\"\n    if user_profile.exists():\n        profile = load_profile(user_profile)\n        return _resolve_inheritance(profile)\n    \n    # 3. Built-in profile\n    name = profile_name or \"repo-brain\"\n    profile = get_builtin_profile(name)\n    return _resolve_inheritance(profile)\n\ndef get_builtin_profile(name: str) -> MemoryProfile:\n    \"\"\"Load a built-in profile by name.\"\"\"\n    profiles_dir = _builtin_profiles_dir()\n    path = profiles_dir / f\"{name}.yaml\"\n    if not path.exists():\n        available = list_builtin_profiles()\n        raise FileNotFoundError(...)\n    return load_profile(path)\n\ndef list_builtin_profiles() -> list[str]:\n    \"\"\"Return the names of all available built-in profiles.\"\"\"\n    profiles_dir = _builtin_profiles_dir()\n    if not profiles_dir.exists():\n        return []\n    return sorted(p.stem for p in profiles_dir.glob(\"*.yaml\"))\n```\n\n---\n\n## INTEGRATION WITH MEMORY STORE\n\n**File:** `C:/cursor/tapps-brain/src/tapps_brain/store.py` (Lines 115-220)\n\n### Store Initialization\n\n```python\nclass MemoryStore:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        project_root: Path,\n        *,\n        store_dir: str = \".tapps-brain\",\n        profile: Any = None,  # MemoryProfile | None (EPIC-010)\n        # ... other params\n    ) -> None:\n        # EPIC-010: resolve and store the active profile\n        self._profile = self._resolve_profile(project_root, profile)\n    \n    @staticmethod\n    def _resolve_profile(project_root: Path, profile: Any) -> Any:\n        \"\"\"Resolve the active memory profile (EPIC-010).\"\"\"\n        if profile is not None:\n            return profile\n        try:\n            from tapps_brain.profile import resolve_profile as _resolve\n            return _resolve(project_root)\n        except Exception:\n            return None  # Graceful degradation\n    \n    @property\n    def profile(self) -> Any:\n        \"\"\"Return the active MemoryProfile, or None.\"\"\"\n        return self._profile\n```\n\n### Promotion After Reinforcement\n\n**File:** `C:/cursor/tapps-brain/src/tapps_brain/store.py` (Lines 676-711)\n\n```python\ndef reinforce(self, key: str, confidence_boost: float = 0.0) -> MemoryEntry:\n    # ... reinforce entry ...\n    updated = entry.model_copy(update=updates)\n    self._persistence.save(updated)\n    \n    # EPIC-010: Check promotion after reinforcement\n    if self._profile is not None:\n        try:\n            from tapps_brain.promotion import PromotionEngine\n            \n            engine = PromotionEngine(decay_cfg)\n            target_tier = engine.check_promotion(updated, self._profile)\n            if target_tier is not None:\n                old_tier = str(updated.tier)\n                promoted = updated.model_copy(\n                    update={\"tier\": target_tier, \"updated_at\": _utc_now_iso()}\n                )\n                with self._lock:\n                    self._entries[key] = promoted\n                self._persistence.save(promoted)\n                self._persistence.append_audit(\n                    action=\"promote\",\n                    key=key,\n                    extra={\n                        \"from_tier\": old_tier,\n                        \"to_tier\": target_tier,\n                        \"access_count\": updated.access_count,\n                        \"reinforce_count\": updated.reinforce_count,\n                    },\n                )\n                logger.info(\n                    \"memory_promoted\",\n                    key=key,\n                    from_tier=old_tier,\n                    to_tier=target_tier,\n                )\n                return promoted\n        except Exception:\n            logger.debug(\"promotion_check_failed\", key=key, exc_info=True)\n    \n    return updated\n```\n\n---\n\n## DECAY CONFIGURATION FROM PROFILE\n\n**File:** `C:/cursor/tapps-brain/src/tapps_brain/decay.py` (Lines 264-327)\n\nThe profile is converted to a `DecayConfig` for use in decay calculations:\n\n```python\ndef decay_config_from_profile(profile: MemoryProfile) -> DecayConfig:\n    \"\"\"Build a DecayConfig from a MemoryProfile instance.\n    \n    Populates:\n    - layer_half_lives: dict[str, int]\n    - layer_confidence_floors: dict[str, float]\n    - profile_source_ceilings: dict[str, float]\n    - layer_decay_models: dict[str, str]\n    - layer_decay_exponents: dict[str, float]\n    - layer_importance_tags: dict[str, dict[str, float]]\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\nThe decay engine uses this config to:\n1. Look up per-layer half-lives\n2. Apply per-layer confidence floors\n3. Use per-layer decay models (exponential vs power-law)\n4. Apply importance tag multipliers to effective half-life\n\n---\n\n## MCP TOOLS FOR PROFILE MANAGEMENT\n\n**File:** `C:/cursor/TappMCP/packages/tapps-mcp/src/tapps_mcp/server_memory_tools.py` (Lines 1696-1850)\n\n### profile_info Action\n\nShows the active memory profile with layer details, decay config, and scoring weights:\n\n```python\ndef _handle_profile_info(store: MemoryStore, _p: _Params) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Handle profile_info action -- show active profile details.\"\"\"\n    # Returns:\n    # {\n    #     \"action\": \"profile_info\",\n    #     \"active_profile\": str,\n    #     \"description\": str,\n    #     \"source\": \"default\" | \"project_override\" | \"user_global\",\n    #     \"layers\": [\n    #         {\n    #             \"name\": str,\n    #             \"description\": str,\n    #             \"half_life_days\": int,\n    #             \"decay_model\": str,\n    #             \"confidence_floor\": float,\n    #             \"promotion_to\": str | None,\n    #             \"demotion_to\": str | None,\n    #         },\n    #         ...\n    #     ],\n    #     \"scoring_weights\": {\n    #         \"relevance\": float,\n    #         \"confidence\": float,\n    #         \"recency\": float,\n    #         \"frequency\": float,\n    #     },\n    #     \"promotion_enabled\": bool,\n    #     \"limits\": {\n    #         \"max_entries\": int,\n    #         \"max_value_length\": int,\n    #     },\n    # }\n```\n\n### profile_list Action\n\nLists all available built-in profiles:\n\n```python\ndef _handle_profile_list(_store: MemoryStore, _p: _Params) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    # Returns:\n    # {\n    #     \"action\": \"profile_list\",\n    #     \"profiles\": [\n    #         {\n    #             \"name\": str,\n    #             \"description\": str,\n    #             \"layers\": int,\n    #             \"decay_models\": [str, ...],\n    #         },\n    #         ...\n    #     ],\n    #     \"total\": int,\n    # }\n```\n\n### profile_switch Action\n\nSwitches to a different memory profile and persists the choice:\n\n```python\ndef _handle_profile_switch(store: MemoryStore, p: _Params) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Handle profile_switch action -- switch to a different memory profile.\"\"\"\n    # 1. Validates target profile name\n    # 2. Persists choice to {project_root}/.tapps-brain/profile.yaml\n    # 3. Resets the memory store singleton cache\n    # Returns:\n    # {\n    #     \"action\": \"profile_switch\",\n    #     \"previous_profile\": str,\n    #     \"active_profile\": str,\n    #     \"changed\": bool,\n    #     \"layers\": str,  # Summary like \"pattern (60d), context (14d), ...\"\n    #     \"description\": str,\n    #     \"store_metadata\": {...},\n    # }\n```\n\nThe profile choice is persisted as:\n```yaml\nprofile:\n  name: \"research-knowledge\"\n  extends: \"research-knowledge\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## TEST COVERAGE\n\n**File:** `C:/cursor/tapps-brain/tests/unit/test_promotion.py`\n\nComprehensive test suite for promotion/demotion including:\n- Promotion triggers at threshold\n- No promotion below access count\n- No promotion without threshold definition\n- No promotion at top tier\n- Demotion on stale entries\n- Desirable difficulty bonus calculations\n- Stability growth calculations\n\n---\n\n## KEY INSIGHTS\n\n1. **Profile Structure:** Each profile defines a hierarchical memory system with configurable decay, confidence management, and automatic tier promotion/demotion.\n\n2. **Promotion Triggers:** A memory is automatically promoted when it meets ALL three criteria:\n   - Minimum access count (e.g., 10 accesses to \"pattern\" layer)\n   - Minimum age (e.g., 30 days in \"pattern\" layer)\n   - Minimum effective confidence (e.g., 0.7 after decay)\n\n3. **Decay Models:** Profiles support both exponential (default) and power-law decay, with per-layer customization.\n\n4. **Importance Tags:** Profiles can define importance tag multipliers (e.g., \"critical\" → 2.0×) that boost effective half-life.\n\n5. **Profile Resolution:** Dynamic resolution allows project-specific, user-global, or built-in defaults.\n\n6. **Integration:** The promotion engine is automatically triggered on `reinforce()` calls and uses the active profile's thresholds to determine promotions.\n\n7. **Source Confidence:** Different sources (human, agent, inferred, system) start with different confidence levels and have different ceilings, preventing agent-source noise from dominating.\n\n---\n\n## FILE PATHS (Absolute)\n\n- `C:/cursor/tapps-brain/src/tapps_brain/profiles/repo-brain.yaml` - Default profile YAML\n- `C:/cursor/tapps-brain/src/tapps_brain/profile.py` - Profile models and loading logic\n- `C:/cursor/tapps-brain/src/tapps_brain/promotion.py` - Promotion/demotion engine\n- `C:/cursor/tapps-brain/src/tapps_brain/store.py` - MemoryStore with profile integration\n- `C:/cursor/tapps-brain/src/tapps_brain/decay.py` - Decay engine using profile config\n- `C:/cursor/tapps-brain/tests/unit/test_promotion.py` - Promotion engine tests\n- `C:/cursor/TappMCP/packages/tapps-mcp/src/tapps_mcp/server_memory_tools.py` - MCP tool handlers for profile management"}],"totalDurationMs":66546,"totalTokens":83207,"totalToolUseCount":35,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1131,"cache_read_input_tokens":77417,"output_tokens":4656,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1131},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
