{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_016MnnbUNSXEfAoZfPcwZupQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the task. The repo-brain profile already has promotion thresholds defined in the YAML file. The task M4 says:\n\n\"Enable promotion engine in default `repo-brain` profile (requires tapps-brain v1.1.0). Set thresholds: context->procedural (3 accesses, 7d), procedural->pattern (5, 14d), pattern->architectural (10, 30d).\"\n\nBut from the exploration, the current thresholds in repo-brain.yaml are:\n- context → procedural: 5 accesses, 7d, 0.5 confidence\n\n\n- procedural → pattern: 8 accesses, 14d, 0.6 confidence  \n- pattern → architectural: 10 accesses, 30d, 0.7 confidence\n\nSo I need to adjust the first two thresholds to match what the task specifies: lowering context→procedural from 5 to 3 accesses, and procedural→pattern from 8 to 5 accesses. The pattern→architectural threshold is already correct at 10 accesses. I should update these values in the repo-brain.yaml file in the tapps-brain repo. Now I need to check the current repo-brain.yaml file to see what the existing thresholds are and update them accordingly.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2225,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5258,"cache_read_input_tokens":28927,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5258},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b61393de-68e8-4cff-8475-056605bcfefe","uuid":"33e1e227-247e-4b99-b039-7b97fa3e0c0e"}
